On January 20, 2009, the White House Office of the Press Secretary announced the nominations sent to the Senate for various positions in the new administration. Some of the nominations included Steven Chu for Secretary of Energy, Hillary Rodham Clinton for Secretary of State, and Thomas Andrew Daschle for Secretary of Health and Human Services. Other nominees included Shaun L.S. Donovan for Secretary of Housing and Urban Development, Arne Duncan for Secretary of Education, and Timothy F. Geithner for Secretary of the Treasury. The list also included nominations for Attorney General, Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency, United States Trade Representative, Secretary of Transportation, Secretary of Homeland Security, Director of the Office of Management and Budget, Representative of the United States to the United Nations, and various other positions.